The EntityEmitter (7) type is used to apply sounds to an entity.


Often used for entities that produce sounds, such as vending machines, air con units and fans.

Fields:

Field name     Type      FileRef Description
--
Name           metahash          EntityEmitter name.
Flags          flags             Unknown flags.
Unk01          metahash  dat54   Main sound.
Unk02          float             Unknown
Unk03          float             Unknown
Unk04          float             Unknown
Unk05          float             Unknown
Unk06          float             Unknown
Unk07          float             Unknown
Unk08          float             Unknown
Unk09          metahash          Unknown //Unused
Unk10          integer           Unknown
Unk11          float             Unknown

Example:

<Item type="EntityEmitter" ntOffset="27951">
 <Name>ee_can_machine</Name>
 <Flags value="0xAAAA9A2A" />
 <Unk01>appliances_can_machine</Unk01>
 <Unk02 value="30" />
 <Unk03 value="0.8" />
 <Unk04 value="0.8" />
 <Unk05 value="0.8" />
 <Unk06 value="0" />
 <Unk07 value="0" />
 <Unk08 value="0" />
 <Unk09 />
 <Unk10 value="2" />
 <Unk11 value="-1" />
</Item>